    </div>
    <div class="content">
      <h2>4. The impacts of the fires crosses borders</h2>
      <p>Smoke from wildfires can travel great distances. It is often pushed into the stratosphere by the heat from fires. Smoke from bushfires in Australia has drifted across the Pacific and may have reached the Antarctic, according to the World Meteorological Organization. This has led to hazardous air quality in major cities throughout Australia, and affected New Zealand and cities in South America after smoke reached both Argentina and Chile.</p>
      <img src="/static/img/list5.jpg" width="660px" />
      <h3>Smoke from the 2019-2020 Australian bushfires is seen from space drifting across the Pacific Ocean. Source: NASA</h3>
